1. Create new user "test_user" and add him to sudoers:
   - by means of group
   - by means of file

2. Connect via ssh to linux server from CLI using username/password from linux host#2
3. Create ssh keys for "test_user" on linux host#2
3. Copy public ssh key to linux server
4. Connect via ssh to linux server from linux host#2 using SSH keys

5. Check all users logged to the server
6. Copy /etc/passwd file from linux server to linux host#2 via SCP to /var/tmp/ folder:
   - from linux host#2
   - from linux server to linux host#2

